{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/background-information/definition/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"2ec7ca08-f644-50e8-b54e-c6378c7053b0","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field f752e576-863e-4145-96ea-3febb16f6b6c --><h2>What is it?</h2><!-- end field f752e576-863e-4145-96ea-3febb16f6b6c -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 61bcc7c9-f2b1-4c74-ae87-a68e0df570c4 --><!-- begin field 7cf449d4-d1e4-4b22-b7b1-f31525d88197 --><ul><li><strong>Raynaud's phenomenon is episodic vasospasm of the arteries or arterioles in the extremities (usually the digits) which leads to colour change including:</strong><ul><li>Pallor (due to decreased blood flow), followed by:</li><li>Cyanosis (due to deoxygenation), and/or</li><li>Rubor (due to reactive hyperaemia) — may be associated with significant discomfort.</li></ul></li><li><strong>The most common triggers for Raynaud’s phenomenon</strong> are exposure to cold and to emotional stress.</li><li><strong>Raynaud’s phenomenon can be classified as</strong>:<ul><li><strong>Primary (or idiopathic) Raynaud's phenomenon</strong> which occurs without an associated <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/background-information/causes-of-or-diseases-associated-with-raynauds-phenomenon/\">underlying condition</a>.</li><li><strong>Secondary Raynaud's phenomenon</strong> which occurs in association with an <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/background-information/causes-of-or-diseases-associated-with-raynauds-phenomenon/\">underlying cause</a> (often a connective tissue disorder).</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">Hughes, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">Ennis, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">Khouri, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">Silva, 2016</a>]  [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">Belch, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">Rirash, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/raynauds-phenomenon/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2019</a>]</p><!-- end field 7cf449d4-d1e4-4b22-b7b1-f31525d88197 --><!-- end item 61bcc7c9-f2b1-4c74-ae87-a68e0df570c4 -->","topic":{"id":"255ee7a1-48e0-54c2-a732-4e03fba17a60","topicId":"e0f3a627-69e7-4258-bfd3-06ad68e3ba94","topicName":"Raynaud's phenomenon","slug":"raynauds-phenomenon","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2020","chapters":[{"id":"0209e319-b6f4-5f73-ae5c-6afd753453ea","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9bb70ded-aa7a-5909-9d84-111f559bccc8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"47c14b87-688e-5e8e-af1c-e6614c461561","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"ad9e53ac-9556-5bdd-aa04-09e22fccd689","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"aa95064f-a6c4-5317-a6ec-33fca3665fa5","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"0346daa7-fb38-5512-b2c8-7f0d5d4b7c91","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"074b9165-8cc3-56b5-a9fa-483516a026aa","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"dadcf48d-9a98-54cf-baab-c0b65179b8f1","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"d272b294-ed60-5488-8640-d756cbe670a3","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteri